WEBVTT

00:01.002 --> 00:03.001
☺ Subbed by BARFNUTS ☺

00:03.002 --> 00:05.671
All right, Dermott, it's time
for you to go home.

00:05.755 --> 00:07.423
Why are you two dressed
like that?

00:07.507 --> 00:11.177
Hey, don't put your heteronormative
gender-biased hang-ups on me.

00:11.260 --> 00:14.430
Boys can play dress-up, too.
Hey, can Dermott spend the night?

00:14.514 --> 00:16.933
Dermott can spend the night
if Dermott takes out the garbage.

00:17.016 --> 00:18.684
It's Thursday.

00:18.768 --> 00:20.978
Dude, what's up with
your dad?

00:21.062 --> 00:22.146
Now he's giving me chores?

00:22.230 --> 00:24.482
Listen, you're complaining
to the wrong guy.

00:24.565 --> 00:28.152
Garbage was my job
'til 10 seconds ago.

00:28.236 --> 00:30.196
Lights out.
It's 11:00.

00:30.279 --> 00:31.948
DEAN:
They are!

00:32.031 --> 00:34.700
- Candles count as lights.
- What are you, a psychic?

00:34.784 --> 00:36.410
They're vanilla
Christmas candles, Dean.

00:36.494 --> 00:38.162
The whole attic smells
like cupcakes.

00:38.246 --> 00:41.207
Now, I'm expecting a call,
so stay off the phone tonight.

00:41.290 --> 00:43.084
You're destroying
my life!

00:43.167 --> 00:45.753
Okay. 10 minutes.
And no sexting.

00:45.836 --> 00:47.213
Do you even know what
that means?

00:47.296 --> 00:49.215
G.Y.P.O.
I'm F.O.L.

00:49.298 --> 00:51.008
Code 9. T.T.Y.L.

00:51.092 --> 00:52.635
That's "Get your pants off.
I'm fond of leather.

00:52.718 --> 00:55.263
My parent or guardian is near.
I will talk to you later"

00:55.346 --> 00:57.014
in sexting language.

00:57.098 --> 00:59.517
Daddy is hip to it, Dean.
10 minutes!

00:59.600 --> 01:02.186
DERMOTT:
So he's been doing this every night?

01:02.270 --> 01:04.605
HANK: I got him to do it
for six hours last night.

01:04.688 --> 01:07.024
Most of the time, he falls
asleep right in the middle.

01:07.108 --> 01:09.277
I find him the next morning
asleep with a phone in his hand.

01:09.360 --> 01:11.070
This will work.

01:11.153 --> 01:13.197
No! Of course I do!

01:13.281 --> 01:15.658
I would've called earlier
if my dad didn't --

01:15.741 --> 01:17.535
N-No, d-don't say that.

01:17.618 --> 01:19.537
Y-You know he just --

01:19.620 --> 01:22.123
But I do! I love you.

01:22.206 --> 01:24.375
No! I love you!

01:24.458 --> 01:26.502
No, I mean it, I just --
[click]

01:26.586 --> 01:28.796
Dad! Get off the phone!

01:28.879 --> 01:31.382
Three more
minutes, Dean.

01:31.465 --> 01:32.800
[ Watch beeps ]

01:32.883 --> 01:36.679
Are you ready for "operation
keep your dad from bugging us"?

01:36.762 --> 01:38.097
Check.

01:38.180 --> 01:40.683
Dialing in "T" minus
10 seconds.

01:40.766 --> 01:42.393
Check.
Bluetooth activated?

01:42.476 --> 01:44.353
Check.
Teddy doll activated?

01:44.437 --> 01:46.397
[whirring ]
- Check.

01:46.480 --> 01:47.523
Begin transmission.

01:47.607 --> 01:48.608
[ringing]

01:48.691 --> 01:51.152
DOC:
Yello? Ted, I presume?

01:51.235 --> 01:53.571
[chuckles]
How's it hangin', player?

01:53.654 --> 01:55.698
Hello. I'm Teddy.

01:55.781 --> 01:58.117
Would you like me to tell you
a story?

01:58.200 --> 01:59.577
Bring it on,
my man.

01:59.660 --> 02:02.997
TEDDY: By Golly Gulch is home
to so many friends --

02:03.080 --> 02:05.458
friends like Grumble Bee
and Lady Bugbear.

02:05.541 --> 02:08.419
But it's also home
to Grumpy Bandersnatch.

02:08.502 --> 02:10.338
Everyone from By Golly Gulch knows

02:10.420 --> 02:13.883
that Grumpy Bandersnatch
hates sliding down rainbows

02:13.966 --> 02:16.385
and never plays with us
in the Honey River.

02:16.469 --> 02:18.262
All right.
Well, there's your problem --

02:18.346 --> 02:20.056
Grumpy doesn't ever play
in the Honey River.

02:20.139 --> 02:21.599
You said "never"?

02:21.682 --> 02:24.268
He just wants to steal
our happiness.

02:24.352 --> 02:25.770
Exactly. You can't expect
a guy like that

02:25.853 --> 02:27.313
To know what you've been
through.

02:27.396 --> 02:29.440
<i>He doesn't swim
in the Honey River.</i>

02:29.523 --> 02:31.317
<i>Well, not like I do that much
myself these days.</i>

02:31.400 --> 02:33.653
He'll go on for hours
without taking a breath.

02:33.736 --> 02:36.322
He doesn't talk to people --
he talks at them.

02:36.405 --> 02:38.783
Cool. All right, let's move.
We go on third.

02:38.866 --> 02:40.284
HANK: Sweet!

02:40.368 --> 02:43.204
DERMOTT:
Yeah, but like eight bands, though.

02:45.414 --> 02:48.834
[rock music playing]

02:48.918 --> 02:50.461
[cellphone vibrating]

02:50.544 --> 02:52.672
Stop! Hold up!
My ass is vibrating!

02:52.755 --> 02:56.008
Me too! The hair on the back
of my neck is standing up!

02:56.092 --> 02:57.760
We are awesome!

02:57.843 --> 02:59.637
[scoffs]
It's your freakin' dad again.

02:59.720 --> 03:01.305
He's been calling every five
minutes for a week.

03:01.389 --> 03:04.183
He's going through
Teddy-Talk-to-Me-doll withdrawal.

03:04.266 --> 03:07.019
"Doll withdrawal."
Hey, say that. It's hard.

03:07.103 --> 03:08.771
Doll withdrawal.
[feedback]

03:08.854 --> 03:10.398
Doll withdrawal.
Yeah, it is.

03:10.481 --> 03:12.483
[cellphone vibrates]
Oh, your dad's calling again.

03:12.566 --> 03:14.360
This is nuts!
We gotta tell him.

03:14.443 --> 03:16.320
Oh, yeah.
"Oh, hey, Mr. V.

03:16.404 --> 03:18.781
Your best friend is a talking doll.
Wicked sorry.

03:18.864 --> 03:20.533
Oh, you're pissed?

03:20.616 --> 03:22.910
But we just did it to pick up
chicks at a bar."

03:22.993 --> 03:24.495
We never picked up chicks.

03:24.578 --> 03:25.621
I'm not going down for this

03:25.705 --> 03:27.790
and looking like a pussy
at the same time.

03:27.873 --> 03:29.500
We picked up chicks.

03:29.583 --> 03:31.335
- [ Beeps]
- Yeah, right, H.E.L.P.Er.

03:31.419 --> 03:33.379
Yeah, I'll believe that
when the Ms. Pac-man table

03:33.462 --> 03:34.505
calls you back.

03:34.588 --> 03:36.465
Dude, you can
understand H.E.L.P.Er now?

03:36.549 --> 03:39.176
- Yeah, wh-- how did I do that?
- I don't even know how I do it.

03:39.260 --> 03:40.845
- [ Beeps ]
- You're both right.

03:40.928 --> 03:42.722
But we'll get slaughtered
if we tell him.

03:42.805 --> 03:45.433
Honestly, how far can
he take this?

03:45.516 --> 03:48.602
The number's to a prepaid
cellphone, Doc.

03:48.686 --> 03:49.520
It's untraceable.

03:49.603 --> 03:50.771
That's what I thought.

03:50.855 --> 03:51.814
Yup. He's in trouble.

03:51.897 --> 03:53.566
Grumpy Bandersnatch.

03:53.649 --> 03:55.484
I told him if he associates
with these gangsters,

03:55.568 --> 03:57.361
they'll eventually get him.

03:57.445 --> 03:59.697
Well, what do we have here?

03:59.780 --> 04:00.698
No bugs, huh?

04:00.781 --> 04:03.492
Did he ever actually say that
he's in danger?

04:03.576 --> 04:04.827
I know the signs,
Hatred!

04:04.910 --> 04:07.413
I'm not some overreacting
first-timer!

04:07.496 --> 04:09.957
Aha! Looks like this leads
right up to --

04:10.040 --> 04:11.834
Right up to my tracing gear.

04:11.917 --> 04:14.545
Doc, y-you saw me plug that in
20 minutes ago.

04:14.628 --> 04:16.505
Okay, fine.
We're safe in here.

04:16.589 --> 04:18.966
I'm gonna check Hank's room.
You check Dean's.

04:19.048 --> 04:20.885
He... won't let me
in there.

04:20.968 --> 04:22.678
HANK:
If you're already holding the guitar,

04:22.762 --> 04:24.555
I don't get why you don't
just play it.

04:24.638 --> 04:27.558
- [ Beeps]
- I can, too! I totally shred.

04:27.641 --> 04:29.560
I just don't have an amp.
You know, we should get one

04:29.643 --> 04:32.271
with the profits from the sales
of our "Jacket" single.

04:32.354 --> 04:34.398
11 cents?
On a check I can't even cash

04:34.482 --> 04:36.692
'cause it's made out to
"Shallow Gravy"?

04:36.776 --> 04:40.529
Okay, boys.
We need to talk.

04:40.613 --> 04:42.573
- [ Beeps]
- H.E.L.P.Er, you puss!

04:42.656 --> 04:44.992
- This can be explained.
- Oh, I'm sure of that.

04:45.075 --> 04:46.994
Yeah, I-I-I have to go home.

04:47.077 --> 04:49.747
- You're a part of this, too, Dermott.
- Okay, but it's Hank's fault.

04:49.830 --> 04:52.750
No! It's my fault.
I let this happen.

04:52.833 --> 04:55.002
I associated
with the wrong sort,

04:55.085 --> 04:57.296
and I've jeopardized
the safety of my family.

04:57.379 --> 04:58.672
I went against my better judgment

04:58.756 --> 05:01.008
and befriended
an ex-criminal named Ted.

05:01.091 --> 05:03.302
Suddenly he disappears,
and I smell foul play.

05:03.385 --> 05:05.888
I search for bugs,
and I find this.

05:05.971 --> 05:07.765
It's a tape of everything

05:07.848 --> 05:09.350
Ted ever said to me
on the phone,

05:09.433 --> 05:11.477
hidden in your stuffed bear.

05:11.560 --> 05:13.521
Boys, we are dealing
with the type of criminal

05:13.604 --> 05:15.731
that would desecrate
a child's toy.

05:15.815 --> 05:17.483
W-Wow. That's --

05:17.566 --> 05:20.319
That's the kind of monster
Grumpy Bandersnatch is!

05:20.402 --> 05:21.987
Now, I don't want
to worry you.

05:22.071 --> 05:24.657
Believe me -- daddy will
handle this.

05:26.367 --> 05:28.494
What are you doing
in my drawer?!

05:28.577 --> 05:30.788
Doc thinks the compounds
been bugged.

05:30.871 --> 05:32.748
I-I was just looking for --
- In my diary?!

05:32.832 --> 05:34.875
I-I think it's a journal,
Dean.

05:34.959 --> 05:36.919
"Diary" is a --
it's a girl's word.

05:37.002 --> 05:38.963
Fine! "Journal"!
Now leave!

05:39.046 --> 05:41.882
You know, I worry about you.
You're looking kind of thin.

05:41.966 --> 05:45.511
Maybe you feel like your life
is spinning out of control?

05:45.594 --> 05:49.056
Maybe the only thing you can
control is your weight?

05:49.139 --> 05:52.059
Dean, are you a friend
of Anna?

05:52.142 --> 05:55.646
- Who's Anna?
- Rexia -- anorexia?

05:55.729 --> 05:58.315
Or do you have another girl
in your life? A-A real --

05:58.399 --> 06:00.150
Oh, my God!
Get out of here!

06:00.234 --> 06:03.654
[telephone ringing]

06:03.737 --> 06:04.780
Bula Vinaka, beachside.

06:04.864 --> 06:07.658
Is it Ted? Keep him on the line.
We need to hook up a trace.

06:07.741 --> 06:09.660
It's for Dean.
I think it's a girl.

06:09.743 --> 06:11.078
BOTH:
Seriously?

06:11.161 --> 06:13.747
Go do something else!
Anything!

06:13.831 --> 06:17.501
HANK: [ muffled ]
Dean! Phone!

06:17.585 --> 06:19.003
Got it!

06:19.086 --> 06:20.212
Hey!

06:20.296 --> 06:22.631
Yeah?
I was just gonna call you.

06:22.715 --> 06:24.592
I-I really want to see you.

06:24.675 --> 06:25.843
Tomorrow?
Tomorrow's perfect!

06:25.926 --> 06:27.970
I can't take it here
anymore.

06:28.053 --> 06:29.847
I love you, too.

06:29.930 --> 06:32.182
I-I-I...
need you, too.

06:32.266 --> 06:35.561
DERMOTT: Uh, wanna hit Taco Bell?
Take a run for the border?

06:35.644 --> 06:37.187
[chuckling ]
Dude, fourth meal.

06:37.271 --> 06:38.772
Eh, Venture lockdown.

06:38.856 --> 06:42.109
No tacos 'til my dad slays
Grumpy Bandersnatch

06:42.192 --> 06:45.362
And frees all the animal friends
of By Golly Gulch.

06:45.446 --> 06:47.823
So stupid.
How does he even believe this?

06:47.907 --> 06:50.242
[ Scoffs ]
Last year, right where you're sitting,

06:50.326 --> 06:52.995
David Bowie, looking
like David Bowie in the '70s,

06:53.078 --> 06:55.414
slapped a guy with invisible
arms and legs.

06:55.497 --> 06:58.083
Right over there, Brock killed
a guy from Dimension "C"

06:58.167 --> 07:00.544
that may or may not have been
an alternate earth.

07:00.628 --> 07:02.546
Dude! Totally see you there!

07:02.630 --> 07:04.256
GARY:
That's impossible! Stealth mode!

07:04.340 --> 07:07.092
HANK: And that's an ex-henchman
for my dad's archenemy.

07:07.176 --> 07:08.928
Pretty sure he lives
in my yard now.

07:09.011 --> 07:12.056
No, no, I get it. I get it.
But we got to fix this.

07:12.139 --> 07:13.349
GARY:
Psst! Hank!

07:13.432 --> 07:15.726
Gary, knock it off!
We can see you!

07:15.809 --> 07:19.438
- Cannot! I'm a shadow.
- I see the top of your head!

07:19.521 --> 07:21.148
I can help.

07:21.231 --> 07:24.151
But the road will be hard
and beset with challenges.

07:24.234 --> 07:26.904
If you accept this offer,
I can only promise you --

07:26.987 --> 07:30.032
upon your victory, you will
finally become men.

07:30.115 --> 07:32.493
[chuckling ]
Okay, guy watching us from the bushes,

07:32.576 --> 07:34.286
you make us into men.

07:34.370 --> 07:36.372
Should I get some lotion,
or do you want to use

07:36.455 --> 07:38.374
