11:30.314 --> 11:32.274
You got to sit down ri--
[grunts ]

11:32.357 --> 11:35.736
Hey! What's going --
Hush-a-bye, my sweet baby.

11:35.819 --> 11:38.822
Mother's here.
It's gonna be okay now.

11:38.906 --> 11:42.659
- I love Mother!
- What a good boy you are!

11:42.743 --> 11:45.245
You've grown into such
a strong boy.

11:45.329 --> 11:46.997
Now take off your clothes

11:47.080 --> 11:49.750
and show mother
your handsome body.

11:51.460 --> 11:54.171
A butterfly.
It's probably Monarch.

11:54.254 --> 11:55.881
Butterfly.

11:55.964 --> 11:57.299
Bigger butterfly.

11:57.382 --> 11:59.301
That's a butterfly, as well.

11:59.384 --> 12:00.469
It's a butterfly again.

12:00.552 --> 12:02.846
Dude, I don't know who's making
these things, but come on.

12:02.930 --> 12:04.890
Seriously, they all look
like butterflies!

12:04.973 --> 12:06.016
What else could they be?

12:06.099 --> 12:09.645
I see... two ladies,
hanked side-by-side.

12:09.728 --> 12:12.856
Between them is me,
Enrrrico Matassa.

12:12.940 --> 12:15.442
They are fighting over the
affections of Enrico Matassa,

12:15.525 --> 12:17.694
I think, but this one
on the left,

12:17.778 --> 12:18.987
she has the husband.

12:19.071 --> 12:20.906
He is not Hank at all.

12:20.989 --> 12:24.201
He is so unHank that he wants
to fight Enrico Matassa!

12:24.284 --> 12:27.746
But Enrico Matassa is
very Hank.

12:27.829 --> 12:29.373
He is double Hank!

12:29.456 --> 12:31.124
Out of the way!
Out of the way!

12:31.208 --> 12:33.669
The prisoner tore the kid's face
off with her teeth!

12:33.752 --> 12:35.170
We're taking him
to the infirmary!

12:35.254 --> 12:37.923
[alarm blaring ]

12:38.006 --> 12:39.341
[ gasping ]

12:39.424 --> 12:41.927
What are you doing?!
You almost broke my neck!

12:42.010 --> 12:45.180
Oh, my collectible
Deanie baby!

12:45.264 --> 12:47.891
Mother just wanted more time
with her boy.

12:47.975 --> 12:51.270
I can't say goodbye anymore!
It's not fair to break up a family!

12:51.353 --> 12:53.563
It's not right!

12:53.647 --> 12:56.358
MAN: All right. Checked with the Guild's
list of subordinates,

12:56.441 --> 12:59.236
manservants,
and boy wonders.

12:59.319 --> 13:01.238
Flying Side Kick's not
on record.

13:01.321 --> 13:03.824
That's because I'm not a boy
wonder -- I'm a regular villain.

13:03.907 --> 13:06.076
It's "Flying Side Kick"
as in the karate move.

13:06.159 --> 13:07.911
Like a side kick, you know,
but in the air.

13:07.995 --> 13:09.997
So you're not another
villain's sidekick,

13:10.080 --> 13:11.498
and you can't fly?

13:11.581 --> 13:14.084
Opening gate 2!
Gotta take the weights off the kid.

13:14.167 --> 13:15.627
He can't really fly.

13:15.711 --> 13:17.379
What -- so I don't need
a ball and chain?

13:17.462 --> 13:19.381
Nah, we haven't used those
in like a hundred years.

13:19.464 --> 13:22.092
I got that one from the, uh,
"old timey jails" display

13:22.175 --> 13:23.760
in the lobby there.

13:23.844 --> 13:26.096
<i>You have arrived
at your destination.</i>

13:26.179 --> 13:30.100
T-This just doesn't look like a --
what was it, gumdrop forest?

13:30.183 --> 13:31.935
I don't know.
Maybe these are gumdrop trees.

13:32.019 --> 13:33.270
I'm not a botanist.

13:33.353 --> 13:35.522
Gumdrop tree--
Doc, these are the kind of trees

13:35.605 --> 13:38.400
that disembowel scarecrows
looking for wizards.

13:38.483 --> 13:41.028
Look, it says "take lniquity
Passage for 8 miles,

13:41.111 --> 13:42.946
arrive at
Bygone Gulch."

13:43.030 --> 13:44.948
Hatred! Bygone gulch?!

13:45.032 --> 13:46.575
We're looking
for By Golly Gulch!

13:46.658 --> 13:48.994
You heard me!
I said "Golly"!

13:49.077 --> 13:51.204
Stupid phone!
We should've used my maps!

13:51.288 --> 13:55.000
- I said "Golly"!
- Hatred! Stop the jeep!

13:55.083 --> 13:57.085
[ Both screaming ]

13:57.919 --> 14:00.213
GARY: Dude, we gotta find
that Teddy guy and get out of here.

14:00.297 --> 14:02.507
I was over crafting
when I was 7 --

14:02.591 --> 14:05.135
not including customizing
my Zoid Liger model, obviously.

14:05.218 --> 14:06.428
[ Normal ]
Obviously.

14:06.511 --> 14:08.805
And why are we making
all these hearts?

14:08.889 --> 14:12.309
And why is mine awesome?
Answer -- doily.

14:12.392 --> 14:14.144
Doily...
doi-ah-lee...

14:14.227 --> 14:16.313
We make these hearts for her.

14:16.396 --> 14:18.899
It's the second Sunday
in May.

14:18.982 --> 14:21.902
We're all Momma's Boys.

14:21.985 --> 14:23.820
Are you a Momma's Boy?

14:23.904 --> 14:26.031
What?! I mean... yeah, of course.
I love my mom.

14:26.114 --> 14:28.992
[Teddy's voice ] Then, brother,
you know today is Mother's Day.

14:29.076 --> 14:29.993
It's her day.

14:30.077 --> 14:32.245
On her day,
we become a family.

14:32.329 --> 14:34.539
Soon, it will be time.

14:34.623 --> 14:36.792
Holy...
you're Teddy-Talk-to-Me!

14:36.875 --> 14:38.168
[laughing]
I think you're mistaken.

14:38.251 --> 14:40.295
Dude! We need your help!

14:40.379 --> 14:42.339
Cuckoo! 5:00!
Cuckoo!

14:42.422 --> 14:44.216
Cuckoo! Clock!

14:44.299 --> 14:46.009
Cuckoo!
Clock!

14:46.093 --> 14:49.388
[indistinct shouting]

14:49.471 --> 14:52.349
Ugh! What happened?
My head...

14:52.432 --> 14:54.059
You got a concussion, there.

14:54.142 --> 14:55.936
Ugh. I feel si--

14:56.019 --> 14:58.814
Nutty buddy!
Bleh...

14:58.897 --> 15:00.357
[sighs]

15:00.440 --> 15:02.442
That's it -- I'm calling
for help.

15:02.526 --> 15:05.195
[watch beeps ]
Hey, Doc. I'm here with you.

15:05.278 --> 15:07.739
We're gonna die together.
Over.

15:07.823 --> 15:10.200
I can't call my morn.
She is nuts.

15:10.283 --> 15:12.202
She signed me up for Al-A-Teen
because I smelled like booze.

15:12.285 --> 15:14.204
Which was only, like,
pheromone spray

15:14.287 --> 15:16.039
cut with a touch of love's
baby soft.

15:16.123 --> 15:17.082
[beeps]

15:17.165 --> 15:19.543
Uh, because I've found that
women are put at ease

15:19.626 --> 15:21.086
when they smell
their own kind.

15:21.169 --> 15:24.673
Seriously. So, do you know, like,
a lawyer or anybody I can call?

15:24.756 --> 15:26.758
- [ Beeps ]
- Really?

15:26.842 --> 15:29.344
Like freakin' Dr. Bombay?
- [ beeps]

15:29.428 --> 15:30.595
All right. I'm gonna try it.

15:30.679 --> 15:32.305
It'll save me a quarter.

15:32.389 --> 15:35.225
[strains]

15:35.308 --> 15:36.518
Whoa!

15:36.601 --> 15:40.105
All those who creep
are now asleep!

15:40.188 --> 15:42.441
Dermott?
How intriguing.

15:42.524 --> 15:45.193
I felt that it was one of
the Venture boys in peril.

15:45.277 --> 15:47.904
So... odd.
- Dude, that was sweet!

15:47.988 --> 15:49.865
Regardless,
let's get you out of here.

15:49.948 --> 15:52.701
Aw, you gonna turn back time
'til, like, before this happened?

15:52.784 --> 15:54.995
Well, no. I'm going
to take your arrest record

15:55.078 --> 15:56.705
off their computer

15:56.788 --> 15:59.541
and get us a taxicab.
- [scoffs ] Gyp.

15:59.624 --> 16:01.626
Oh!
[chuckles] I'm sorry.

16:01.710 --> 16:03.670
Was my appearing from thin air

16:03.753 --> 16:06.131
and putting everyone to sleep
a disappointment?

16:06.214 --> 16:09.009
You see that kind of magical
fun constantly, I assume?

16:09.092 --> 16:10.927
Not cool enough for you?

16:11.011 --> 16:12.095
- TOGETHER: Mother!
- Cuckoo!

16:12.179 --> 16:13.305
TOGETHER:
Mother!

16:13.388 --> 16:14.473
- Mother!
- Cuckoo! Cuckoo!

16:14.556 --> 16:18.226
TOGETHER:
Mother! Mother! Mother!

16:18.310 --> 16:21.104
All my little babies!

16:21.188 --> 16:24.566
We are finally a family!

16:24.649 --> 16:27.277
Mother doesn't judge
her sweet children.

16:27.360 --> 16:30.739
You're free -- free to be
yourselves now!

16:30.822 --> 16:32.491
Mm... that's my morn,
I think.

16:32.574 --> 16:34.326
Maybe Man! Big Time!

16:34.409 --> 16:37.037
Can you do mommy
your special favor now?

16:37.120 --> 16:38.121
- Yes, mother!
- Maybe!

16:38.205 --> 16:39.873
Could you return me
to the day

16:39.956 --> 16:42.834
when my little baby Dean
was born?

16:42.918 --> 16:45.754
Of course!
There's time for that!

16:45.837 --> 16:47.631
Aren't you a good boy.

16:47.714 --> 16:49.466
And, Maybe Man, could you
put baby Dean

16:49.549 --> 16:52.177
in my pink, pillowy womb

16:52.260 --> 16:56.723
so I can finally give birth
to my teeny-weenie Deanie

16:56.806 --> 17:00.185
and be his only-wonly mommy?

17:00.268 --> 17:02.521
Um... Maybe.

17:02.604 --> 17:04.981
"Finally give birth"?
You're not my mother!

17:05.065 --> 17:06.608
I knew you were lying!

17:06.691 --> 17:10.069
Hanky-poo?!
You've come to me!

17:10.153 --> 17:12.405
I'm not a Hank--
She is not my mother!

17:12.489 --> 17:14.616
Yeah!
She's not my mother, either!

17:14.699 --> 17:17.702
I'm The Viceroy!
I wanna be a Monarch!

17:17.786 --> 17:19.079
Butterfly, I mean!

17:19.162 --> 17:21.330
No! She's not my mother!

17:21.414 --> 17:24.876
I'm Teddy!
I wanna slide down rainbows!

17:24.960 --> 17:28.505
And I'm Radical Left!
I want anarchy!

17:28.588 --> 17:31.216
And -- and maybe a nice home
and a family.

17:31.299 --> 17:34.219
Yeah!
Mother helped build the wall!

17:34.302 --> 17:35.971
Tear down the wall!

17:36.054 --> 17:38.181
MOTHER: Play nice, everybody!
Shake hands, you two!

17:38.265 --> 17:40.183
[indistinct shouting]

17:40.267 --> 17:42.811
Settle down! Settle down!

17:42.894 --> 17:45.063
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

17:45.146 --> 17:46.898
[ Muffled screaming ]

17:46.982 --> 17:50.110
MOTHER:
No! No! My sweet babies! No!

17:50.193 --> 17:52.195
[indistinct screaming]

17:55.448 --> 17:58.660
Get going!
I'll get your brother!

17:58.743 --> 18:00.662
HATRED:
That is your worst death confession?

18:00.745 --> 18:02.205
That? Really?

18:02.289 --> 18:04.124
What? I let her believe she was
the boy's mother.

18:04.207 --> 18:05.667
I messed her up pretty bad.

18:05.750 --> 18:08.253
Beats your "I was an O.S.Il.
Traitor, boo hoo" nonsense.

18:08.336 --> 18:11.381
All right, all right! Here -- you see
these man boobs here?

18:11.464 --> 18:13.425
Well, they kinda
turn me on.

18:13.508 --> 18:15.343
Sometimes I look at them
when I masturbate

18:15.427 --> 18:17.220
and pretend
they're on a lady.

18:17.304 --> 18:19.222
There!
That's a death confession!

18:19.306 --> 18:20.223
I can beat it!

18:20.307 --> 18:23.351
Hank's friend Dermott?
That's my illegitimate son.

18:23.435 --> 18:25.604
Yup -- love child.

18:25.687 --> 18:27.689
Don't act like you're not
impressed.

18:27.772 --> 18:29.608
HATRED:
Wow. All right, you win.

18:29.691 --> 18:31.693
That is... [sighs]
Wow.

18:31.776 --> 18:33.445
[sirens wailing in distance]

18:33.528 --> 18:36.323
[indistinct shouting,
glass breaking]

18:36.406 --> 18:38.617
Aww!
I knew she wasn't our mom.

18:38.700 --> 18:42.537
That would've been a good thing,
and I don't get good things.

18:42.621 --> 18:45.915
Yeah, it's just too bad
that a raving lunatic

18:45.999 --> 18:48.084
that wanted to make you
a baby again

18:48.168 --> 18:49.461
and then push you up
her lady hole

18:49.544 --> 18:51.129
isn't our real morn.

18:51.212 --> 18:52.088
Real tragedy.

18:52.172 --> 18:53.923
Yeah. Good point.

18:54.007 --> 18:56.426
Amazingly, you always have
good points, Hank.

18:56.509 --> 18:59.304
That's "Enrico Matassa,"
my friend.

18:59.387 --> 19:01.181
Ah, there you are.
Yeah, I couldn't find Teddy.

19:01.264 --> 19:02.849
It's a madhouse in there.

19:02.932 --> 19:04.559
I mean, it was a madhouse
to begin with, but --

19:04.643 --> 19:06.561
well, you know what I mean.
- Eh, don't worry.

19:06.645 --> 19:09.397
We'll just tell my dad that we...
went to save Dean.

19:09.481 --> 19:11.274
What?
You didn't come to save me?

19:11.358 --> 19:12.400
[helicopter blades whirring]

19:12.484 --> 19:15.153
GARY: Aw, geez.
Guild wasps. We gotta haul.

19:15.236 --> 19:16.446
DOC:
It's effortless.

19:16.529 --> 19:18.657
We're just tuned
into each other.

19:18.740 --> 19:22.160
Ironic that my bestie is
a dust head and my ex-kidnapper.

19:22.243 --> 19:23.787
He kidnapped you?

19:23.870 --> 19:26.081
Yeah, about a year ago, when
all those scientists were taken.

19:26.164 --> 19:28.792
He was working with these guys
called The Monster and --

19:28.875 --> 19:30.293
Ah, wait, wait.
Don't tell me --

19:30.377 --> 19:32.295
a guy with
a robot voice, right?

19:32.379 --> 19:33.421
Yeah, that was him.

19:33.505 --> 19:35.298
Ted just gets mixed up
with these guys,

19:35.382 --> 19:38.343
like Grumpy Bandersnatch
and that robot guy.

19:38.426 --> 19:41.638
He's got to stop swinging from
gumdrop trees and grow up.

19:41.721 --> 19:44.307
[chuckles]
I guess I'm like a mentor to him.

19:44.391 --> 19:46.351
Doc...
[sighs ] Ah, geez.

19:46.434 --> 19:49.062
I got to tell you something
about Ted.

19:49.145 --> 19:50.814
You're not gonna like this
at all.

19:50.897 --> 19:53.108
[ Rumbling, grinding ]
Hatred, stop moving!

19:53.191 --> 19:55.193
We're sliding again!

19:55.276 --> 19:56.986
TED:
Grab the branch!

19:57.070 --> 19:59.739
Your buggy is about to slide
down the gulch!

19:59.823 --> 20:01.366
Ted?!

20:01.449 --> 20:03.451
[grunting ]

20:07.914 --> 20:10.208
ORPHEUS:
It's not a DNA test.

20:10.291 --> 20:12.085
I'm simply saying
that when you summoned me,

20:12.168 --> 20:14.170
I felt the mind
of a Venture boy.

20:14.254 --> 20:15.922
So... I'm a Venture?

20:16.005 --> 20:18.383
Magic reveals
little more than questions.

20:18.466 --> 20:21.428
She is a capricious light
that tickles the intellect

20:21.511 --> 20:25.807
and begs us to peer into
the newly illuminated truth.

20:25.890 --> 20:27.767
Yeah, that's,
uh, totally confusing.

20:27.851 --> 20:29.811
Then I, again,
have done my job.

20:29.894 --> 20:31.604
Well if, you know,
I'm a Venture,

20:31.688 --> 20:34.190
then can you give me
your daughter's new number?

20:34.274 --> 20:37.110
- Not from beyond the grave, Dermott.

20:37.193 --> 20:38.361
[grunting ]

20:38.445 --> 20:41.156
I come to save you,
and you end up saving me.

20:41.239 --> 20:42.699
[laughs]
How about that?

20:42.782 --> 20:45.535
I love you.
You're my best friend.

20:45.618 --> 20:48.288
Now I have to return
to my Lady Bugbear

20:48.371 --> 20:51.666
and all my friends
in By Golly Gulch.

20:51.750 --> 20:53.418
Call me,
you rascal!

20:53.501 --> 20:56.379
And give your Ladybug a slap on
the fanny for me, player!

20:56.463 --> 20:58.423
[chuckles]
Ahhhh.

20:58.506 --> 20:59.799
You see what I'm saying?

20:59.883 --> 21:02.385
He's a bit out there,
but just true blue.

21:02.469 --> 21:04.012
Now, what were you gonna
tell me about him?

21:04.095 --> 21:07.766
Uh, that, uhh... he's a...
burn victim?

21:07.849 --> 21:09.184
- Oh, my God. Right?

21:09.267 --> 21:11.686
That nose --
[shudders]

21:11.770 --> 21:15.273
[ Shallow Gravy's "Diearrhea" plays]

21:15.356 --> 21:17.233
♪ Come on, smell it ♪

21:17.317 --> 21:19.611
♪ Feel the diarrhation ♪

21:22.530 --> 21:23.948
- ♪ They all died of ♪
- ♪ Diarrhea ♪

21:24.032 --> 21:25.658
- ♪ Thomas Jefferson had ♪

21:25.742 --> 21:26.910
- ♪ Diarrhea ♪

21:26.993 --> 21:28.286
- ♪ James K. Polk had ♪

21:28.369 --> 21:29.496
- ♪ Diarrhea ♪

21:29.579 --> 21:30.914
♪ William Henry Harrison ♪

21:30.997 --> 21:32.248
♪ Yeah ♪

21:32.332 --> 21:34.334
♪ They all died ♪

21:39.422 --> 21:41.090
DOC:
By the time we found the hover tank

21:41.174 --> 21:43.343
and removed the like 40
parking tickets on it,

21:43.426 --> 21:45.094
we figured it was
too late to call, so...

21:45.178 --> 21:46.971
Oh, we had
an interesting night, too.

21:47.055 --> 21:49.432
We were saving Dean from Myra,

21:49.516 --> 21:51.976
who's not our mom,
apparently...?

21:52.060 --> 21:53.770
Yeah...
Daddy makes mistakes, Hank.

21:53.853 --> 21:55.688
You boys needed free daycare,

21:55.772 --> 21:57.524
and when Myra was younger,

21:57.607 --> 22:00.318
she was quite
the sexual panther.

22:00.401 --> 22:01.903
I needed my daycare, too.

22:01.986 --> 22:03.780
Oh, gross!
Dude, that's my cue.

22:03.863 --> 22:06.574
I don't wanna hear this.
I gotta go to work in two hours.

22:06.658 --> 22:08.159
Later, loser.

22:08.243 --> 22:10.703
Latrix,
my fart-flavored friend.

22:10.787 --> 22:13.164
Yeah, she wore
these little hot pants.

22:13.248 --> 22:14.916
No! I don't wanna hear it,
either!

22:14.999 --> 22:18.878
Oh, uh, later...
Dad.
